-- Czech Banks Forecast GDP to Shrink 0.95 Percent This Year
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2012-10-10T07:26:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-10/czech-banks-forecast-gdp-to-shrink-0-95-percent-this-year.html
The Czech Banking Association
forecast the domestic economy to decline 0.95 percent this year.  Gross domestic product will rise 0.45 percent next year,
the banking association said today in  Prague  in an update of its
economic forecast.  The association expects the total loan portfolio to rise
3.6 percent in 2012, even with the overall economic slowdown, it
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
